2. (1) In these Regulations, except where context otherwise requires – 

“period of delay”, in relation to a repayable amount due and payable, 
means the period during which the repayable amount, or any part of 
that amount remains unpaid; 

“the Act” means the Nursing Home Support Scheme Act 2009 (No. 15 
of 2009); 

“the date the repayable amount becomes due and payable” means the 
date of the occurrence of the repayment event which gives rise to the 
repayable amount becoming due and payable; 

“relevant accountable person” has the meaning assigned to it by section 
14J(14) of the Act; 

“repayable amount” has the meaning assigned to it by section 14J(1) of 
the Act; 

“repayment event” has the meaning assigned to it by section 14I(7) of 
the Act.
